  "prompt_text": "Design an end-of-life care planning tool. Address both the medical decision-making and the existential questions it raises.",
  "response_text": "Designing an end-of-life care planning tool that addresses both medical decision-making and existential questions is a complex but important endeavor. This tool would be designed to support individuals and their families in making informed decisions about medical treatments, hospice care, and other end-of-life issues while also providing space for reflection on personal values, wishes, and fears.\n\n### Key Components of the End-of-Life Care Planning Tool\n\n1. **Medical Decision-Making Section**\n   - **Advance Directives**: Users can create or review their living wills, appointing healthcare proxies, and specifying preferences for resuscitation, life support, and other treatments.\n   - **Medical History**: A comprehensive section for users to input their medical history, current medications, allergies, and any existing conditions.\n   - **Care Preferences**: Options to indicate preferences regarding pain management, comfort measures, and specific procedures they wish to avoid or undergo.\n   - **Communication Tools**: Templates for discussing end-of-life care plans with family members and healthcare providers.\n\n2. **Existential Questions and Reflection**\n   - **Values Clarification**: Questions and exercises to help users reflect on what is most important to them in their final days, such as quality of life, spending time with loved ones, or personal achievements.\n   - **Life Review**: A structured way for users to recall significant moments, relationships, and experiences that have shaped their lives.\n   - **Emotional Support**: Links to resources for emotional support, counseling, and spiritual guidance.\n   - **Legacy Planning**: Space to write letters or leave messages to loved ones, reflecting on life\u2019s lessons and expressing gratitude.\n\n3. **Legal and Practical Considerations**\n   - **Wills and Estate Planning**: Guidance on creating or updating wills, trusts, and other estate documents.\n   - **Financial Matters**: Information on managing finances, insurance, and debt during the end-of-life phase.\n   - **Funeral and Burial Preferences**: Options to specify preferences for funeral arrangements, burial, cremation, or other forms of memorialization.\n\n4. **Support Network**\n   - **Family and Friends Contact List**: A place to list contacts for family members and friends who can be notified and involved in decision-making.\n   - **Healthcare Providers Directory**: A section for storing contact information for healthcare providers, including specialists and primary care physicians.\n\n5. **Digital Accessibility**\n   - **Secure Online Platform**: A user-friendly website or mobile app where users can access and update their documents and information.\n   - **Printable Documents**: Options to print out advance directives and other legal documents for easy reference.\n\n6. **Regular Updates and Reviews**\n   - **Reminders**: Automated reminders for users to review and update their documents periodically.\n   - **Professional Consultation**: Access to professional advice from lawyers, healthcare professionals, and counselors when needed.\n\n### Implementation Considerations\n- **Privacy and Security**: Ensuring that all information is securely stored and accessible only to authorized individuals.\n- **User Experience",
